  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Authorization",
            "value": "Bearer {{token}}"
          }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base}}/api/{{prefix}}/health",
          "host": [
            "{{base}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "{{prefix}}",
            "health"
          ]
        }
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "Create HTML message",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "// Tests: assert 2xx and log JSON or HTML",
              "pm.test(\"Status code is 2xx\", function () {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.within(200, 299);",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Try to parse JSON; if not JSON, log HTML/text safely",
              "(function logResponse() {",
              "    const contentType = pm.response.headers.get(\"Content-Type\") || \"\";",
              "    if (contentType.includes(\"application/json\")) {",
              "        try {",
              "            const data = pm.response.json();",
              "            console.log(\"Response JSON:\", data);",
              "        } catch (e) {",
              "            console.log(\"Response not valid JSON, raw text:\", pm.response.text());",
              "        }",
              "    } else {",
              "        console.log(\"Response text/html:\", pm.response.text());",
              "    }",
              "})();",
              "",
              "/*",
              "Troubleshooting tips for 404 Not Found:",
              "1) Verify base and prefix variables resolve to a valid URL and path.",
              "   - Example values:",
              "     - base: https://your-host.example.com",
              "     - prefix: v1 (or empty if your API path is /api/messages)",
              "   - Full URL would resolve to: {{base}}/api/{{prefix}}/messages -> e.g. https://your-host.example.com/api/v1/messages",
              "2) If your API does not use \"/api\" or \"prefix\", adjust the URL accordingly.",
              "   - Examples:",
              "     - {{base}}/messages",
              "     - {{base}}/api/messages",
              "3) Ensure the collection/environment has variables set:",
              "   - base, prefix, token",
              "   You can inspect resolved values in the console during a run using Postman \"Code\" or hover over variables.",
              "4) Check auth:",
              "   - Authorization header already uses Bearer {{token}}. Confirm token is valid and not expired.",
              "5) Content-Type is set to application/json; body must match your API schema. Current payload:",
              "   {\"subject\":\"Welcome\",\"to\":[\"alice@example.com\"],\"html\":\"<p>Hello</p>\"}",
              "6) If server expects a different route (e.g., /send, /emails, /mail), update the path.",
              "*/"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "packages": {},
            "requests": {}
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Authorization",
            "value": "Bearer {{token}}"
          },
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\"subject\": \"Welcome\", \"to\": [\"visan.silviu@feg.eu\"], \"html\": \"<p>Hello</p>\"}",
          "options": {
            "raw": {
              "language": "json"
            }
          }
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base}}/api/{{prefix}}/messages",
          "host": [
            "{{base}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "{{prefix}}",
            "messages"
          ]
        }
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "Create Template message",
      "request": {
